Word Drills

'class' - Tell Python to make a new type of a thing.
'object' - Two meanings: the most basic type of thing, and any instance of some thing.
'instance' - What you get when you tell Python to create a class.
'def' - How to define a function inside of a class.
'self' - Inside the function in a class, self is variable for  instance/object being accessed.
'inheritance' - The concept that one class can inherit traits from another class as parts, much like how a car has wheels.
'attribute' - A property classes have that are from composition and are usually variables.
'is-a' - A phrase to say that something is inherits from another, as in "salmon" is-a "fish."
'has-a' - A phrase to say that something is composed of other things or has a trait, as in "a salmon has-a mouth."

Phrase Drills

class X(Y) "Make a class named X that is-a Y."
class X(object): def __init__(self, J) "class X has-a __init__ that takes self and J parameters."
class X(object): def M(self, J) "class X has-a function names M that takes self and J parameters."
fee = X() "Set foo to an instance of class X."
foo.M(X) "From foo get M function, and call it with parameters self, J."
foo.K = Q "From foo get the K attribute and set it to Q."
